3. `nth_partial i (nth_partial j f) ((1 - t) • x + t • y)`

The third part, `nth_partial i (nth_partial j f) ((1 - t) • x + t • y)`, is the `i`-th partial derivative of the `j`-th partial derivative of `f`, evaluated at the point `(1 - t) • x + t • y`.

